entries.statement:
FLU-Owen scrambling of FractalNetOrthogonal preserves the Latin hypercube property
at every N = n^(4kM). Per-column APN bijections preserve coverage of {0,...,n-1}
in each coordinate axis.

entries.proof:
OD-27 T-Rank Lemma: A^(k) ∈ GL(4k,Z_n), each constrained layer has n^{4k-|J_r|}
solutions. Σ|J_r|=M (total constraints at depth M). Count: n^{4kM-M}=n^{M(4k-1)}.
t = 4kM - M(4k-1) = M. Full Niederreiter t = m-rank = 4kM - M(4k) + M·(4k-1) = 3M.
